< username>
Valeria<//username>
< text>
If you are looking to enjoy yourself with a great atmosphere and delicious food, The Cove is the place to visit! First let's talk about the food: the portions are on the larger size and the taste, WOW. We got the lamb tenderloins appetizer and it immediately became a favorite! The rosemary sauce that came with the dish was so good I had to save it to eat it with my main dish. All the staff is incredibly nice an attentive too. No complaints at all. The bathroom and the entire place over all is super clean. We watched a live band known as "Those Guys," I seriously think they will blow up and become really famous soon. If you are in Murrieta, California you have to stop by The Cove!<//text>

< Review>
As the world is re-emerging, many companies will struggle a bit with having their institutions conform to transitioning rules. The Cove is a great place for entertainment and food, however they are slightly behind the curve with hiring enough staff to keep maintain a 5 star rating in customer service. Staff is great, there's simply not enough of them.</Review>

<rate>5</rate><Text>Stopped in today for the first time in a couple years (we have moved out of the area).  Awesome!!!!  Food was great (Asian salad, and The Cove burger), both cooked perfectly and tasted awesome.  The drinks were poured well (strong enough to enjoy, but not so strong we were unsafe leaving).  Our bartender, Kelsey (I think?!?  Horrible with names- thin, fit, long dark hair, cute, tattoos,  knew all the regulars) was on point!  Excellent balance of knowing all the regulars, communicating with the other staff, greeting folks as they entered, and making the non-regulars feel welcome and at home. The regulars were friendly and chatty, but none were obnoxious (several were attending a funeral for a local well known coach, considering the emotions involved that speaks well to the type of crowd the place draws).  Overall, we absolutely will be back!  I just wish we still lived in the area to make it by more often.<//Text><GmapID>0x80dc83ebe7de70b1:0xe1a7774c5f58f1a3</GmapID>< Pics>

<user>109761339138481080578< /user><username>Marlon Gonzalez<//username>< text>
We stumbled upon this location fairly early on a Saturday just after indulging in some Intelligensia coffee which is just across the street.  We were greeted by a gentleman who invited us in to take a look inside so we saw no reason not to.  The inside of the store is very sleek, designed almost like an Apple store with different products and strains showcased in the display aisles accompanied by descriptive details about the product.  The sign-up process was painless, the place just opened and it was already getting busy, but it went by very quickly nonetheless.  The entire staff was very cordial and professional.  We winded up settling on an more upbeat, energetic product that was relaxing, but not at all heavy.  Definitely a place to check out if you're in the area, their edible selection was also noteworthy!< /text>

< review>
(Translated by Google) Super professional marijuana shop with a wide variety of products, from general cannabis flowers, cigarette paper, concentrated electronic cigarettes ..., to beverages, chocolates ..., to clothes, candles ... and other peripherals, there are many more cannabis-related products !!

Generally, marijuana shops don't sell lighters. You can also run a cigarette hotel after buying marijuana, but MedMen sells lighters, so you don't have to.

Friends who like marijuana must not miss this store, it's great!

<date>1552918561864</date><Pics>None<//Pics><rating>5<//rating><username>Lydia Dabbs</username>< Review>
Walking into any store these days, especially in California! can often be a discouraging experience. I've noticed anywhere you go...there is a complete lack of customer care, and appretiation. Often you find yourself searching for things you need for hours because typically, you are never offered help anymore...and if you are employees don't even seem to know anything about the products they sell or their way around the store they work in.
My husband and I were searching for our first actual mattress together, we had been sleeping on the worst mattress for many years and at this point ANYTHING would have been better. We planned the day around going from outlet to outlet, and finding the best deal possible. The very first outlet we walked into, we were not greeted, and we had to search for someone to ask a question, the employee then stood there akwardly, and silently (only giving us pricing information) and once we said we'd come back, he was gone.
The second, and FINAL stop was Ortho Inc. in Fountain Valley. We were actually in search of a different store nearby and couldn't find it and so happy we didn't! We walked into, the cleanest, nicest location...and greeted instantly by a bubbly, smiling face...we felt like she was excited to see us...like long lost friends!
The very first thing she did was ask our names and introduce herself (Sunny!!) and engaged in conversation like she had known us forever. She took her time, she mentioned she did not work at this store but you wouldn't know AT ALL, she knew where everything was, and exactly what she wanted to show us. You could tell this women loved her job, and was excited to help us find our first mattress. She did everything she could to help us choose the perfect one. She took her time checking on our financing options, she gave us time to discuss our concerns and offered us a deal we COULD NOT refuse.
We had a bit of concerns and thought we might have to come back, she gave us all of her information and even offered her cell phone number if we had any questions. We made it to the parking lot and within 3 minutes came back in to purchase the bed.
Sunny is amazing, courteous, friendly, and she mde us feel so important. This is truly what world class service is all about and we couldn't imagine going anywhere else, or to anyone else. Thanks, Sunny! You changed our lives in one day! No more back aches, and restless nights.</Review>

< text>
Visited some wineries this weekend while on vacation and Starmont was hands down the best winery I went to all weekend. The staff were very knowledgeable and friendly, the location was convenient, the tasting room and seating area was beautiful, and the wines were fantastic. They have a really lovely fire pit area with comfortable couches and chairs and even blankets you can use if you get a bit chilly. What really made the difference in my mind was the staff. They were really accommodating and just good people all around. Some of the other places we went to, people were a bit snobbish and it felt like they could care less whether you were there or not. I highly recommend the GSM blend and their Chardonnay. Both were pretty fantastic in my opinion.<//text>

<UserId.>116015049792978913842<//UserId.><name>Matthew Frith< /name>< time>
1487492541210< /time>
< Rate>
2</Rate>
< review>
Perhaps I went on a bad day... we arrived around 2pm on a Saturday. We often frequent Napa and Sonoma to pick up our wine club selections and have always noticed starmont when coming in and figured we would try it this time around.We walked in and noticed it was fairly crowded. There is a lot of seating inside of the tasting room and every seat was taken, there was plenty of room at the wine bar though. We walked up and waited patiently. There were 3 workers behind the counter and we waited around 10 minutes and was not acknowledged once. There were 2 other couples there, so I feel that there was at least some time to say we will be with you in a bit or at least a hello... but we sat there and waited. This gave us the opportunity to look around at the crowd. It was a pretty young crowd. Everyone seemed to be 21, which is fine, but it was rather loud and you could hear the random "OMG" once in awhile, similar to a bar. This environment reminded me of my college days and although it was only 6 years ago, it is something that I want nothing to do with. There was even a girl taking multiple selfies, sipping wine and posting it on snapchat. I am a former wine buyer and was disappointed that I was not able to try their wines, but the environment was very off setting. If this place wants to cater to this crowd, that is fine. This review is more aimed at those who want a relaxing environment and, frankly, want semi-decent customer service. If you just turned 21 or are new to wine, then this is the place for you.<//review>

< Review>
WOO-HOO!!!

This place has *THE BEST* Mexican food around here.
& I'm not lying.

If you're looking for great customer service and amazingly fresh and authentic Mexican Cuisine you have to come here!! When have I steered you wrong?

Miguel, one of the owners is always so cheery and helpful--always willing to suggest you the best platter for your needs. I've tried almost their entire menu:

*Pozole
*Menudo
*Tortas de Asada
*Tacos de Al Pastor
*Tacos de Chicharron
*Tacos de Carnitas
*Torta de Jamon
*Tacos de Asada
*Quesadillas
*Asada Fries
*Tamales
*Champurrado
*Aguas Frescas; Guava, Sandia & Horchata!

Looking back at all I've had at this awesome place, EVERY SINGLE MEAL has blown me out of the water. You just have to try this place, already!!

*-Bonus-* Taco Tuesdays= 99 cents!!

You can order for pick-up, or dine-in. There are a couple of tables inside where you can enjoy your hot meal. Can't wait for you to go. I just know you're going to love it.
Let me know how you liked it! ;o)<//Review>

<date>1405701431974</date><Rating>5</Rating><text>I've just started a lease for a Nissan Leaf one week ago. This is the first time I've ever leased a car and this is my first electric car. So far it has been a great experience.

North Bay Nissan was the first stop on my search for an electric car. Guy Crosbie worked with me and my wife explaining the nuances of being an electric car owner and showing what the Nissan Leaf had to offer and it's limitations. We never felt pressured and left feeling very good about the experience. I think Guy knew we were coming back.

We visited a few more dealerships and decided the Leaf was the car for our needs. I called Guy late on a Saturday and he told me to come down. Abel was available to answer some questions to make sure the Leaf would meet my needs, he also owns a Leaf and was very helpful. I got the model and color that I wanted and continued with the sales process. Originally I had intended to buy the car but one of the incentives available for the 2014 model was not available for the 2015 and they were out of 2014's. Guy was very professional with this situation and let me work out the decision with my wife. We worked with Andy in the finance department and he was very helpful. After going through our options and asking a bunch of questions we figured leasing was the better choice. At no point did Andy pressure us in one direction or another and we're very happy with our choice.

Ron's been helping me with figuring out home charging options. He's very knowledgeable and responsive through email. Consistent with the level of service we've experienced at North Bay Nissan.

<username>Sc S< /username><date>1382314023250<//date>< pics>

<Rate>5</Rate><Resp>None<//Resp>< Review>
I have purchased many vehicles, both new and used.  I usually know exactly what I want to buy and pay, and research inventories before I contact dealers.  That was the case with the xTerra Pro that I purchased from North Bay Nissan two weeks ago.  Early on a Monday I called requesting Sales and Bruce took my call.  Told him exactly the vehicle I wanted and requested that we agree on a price quickly over the phone.  We were able to do that with a minimum of calls which I really appreciated.  We then covered a few details, including financing options and other essentials. Bruce also arranged for me to get picked up in San Francisco after I finished work, and in enough time to make the trip to Petaluma before the dealership closed.  These arrangements went perfectly and I arrived about 715p.

Bruce informed  earlier that he would not be working that evening and arranged for Ron to complete the sale and delivery.  The car was cleaned and ready when I arrived.  Ron suggested a quick test drive and then very patiently did a walk-through of all the relevant features and controls.  Ron collected all final details to complete the delivery and financing, and then turned me over to the Finance Manager.    Once I was with the Finance Manager, completing the transaction was quick and painless.

The only downside to the entire transaction was that I had to wait almost an hour and 20 minutes for the Finance Manager to see me.  The date was 9/30 - the end of the month and quarter - and there was only one Finance Manager on duty.  This was really poor planning, especially for a busy sales day.  It was after 10p when i finally left, three hours after arriving.  I had a long drive ahead of me back to San Francisco and work early the next morning.

Bruce and Ron have both called to see how I am enjoying the xTerra and to offer their help if anything needs to be addressed.  The day after the sale I also received a call from the dealership asking for my feedback on the purchase transaction.  This was good follow-up on the sale and very much appreciated.

Bruce and Ron were excellent to work with and I recommend them without reservation .  Even though North Bay Nissan is not at all convenient to San Francisco, I would contact them first if I decide to buy another Nissan.</Review>

<Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
This is the first time I have not felt pressured at a dealership and the first time I was looking forward to writing a review! I was nervous/skeptical about purchasing/leasing an electric car and both Guy Crosbie and Ron Coury were a great team; they not only answered all my questions, but made me feel comfortable, making my concerns go away. They provided me with a pressure free purchase and took the time to explain the wonders of this crazy electric car. They provided me with awesome service and directed me to all the special incentives as well as electric car websites that I can use from my phone while I am commuting (on the side of the road). Guy spent a great deal explaining all the gadgets and extras in the car while Ron explained all the neat features of the "carwings" as well as the online community when it comes to electric cars. Even when I was signing all the paperwork, Sam (Finance Manager) was awesome! We actually had a real conversation and he didn't try and sell me the normal and famous "old school dealership triple undercoat package."  Needless to say, I am very happy with my experience and would not hesitate to recommend Guy, Ron, Sam, and North Bay Nissan; they do it the right way.</review>

<rate>1</rate>< text>
Terrible company, with terrible service. Our Nissan Xterra's transmission failed at 160,000 miles (bummer but it happens), we purchased a brand new transmission through this dealership with a warrantee. The transmission we received was installed and turned out to be faulty. The check engine light kept coming on and this dealership would clear the code and try and blame the mechanic who installed the transmission. We had to bring our car to our mechanic over ten different times leaving it for multiple days on multiple occasions. For a total of over 10 nights. The mechanic brought the car to the dealership multiple times and also had to we bring the car to the dealership. Throughout this process the dealership did absolutely nothing to compensate for the inconvenience, they did not supply a rental car, rarely returned out phone calls, and never gave anything near an apology. After months of phone calls and bringing our car in they finally did a thorough inspection of the transmission which revealed it was in fact faulty and therefore covered by the warrantee. After which they refused to supply the labor to remove the faulty transmission they supplied, refused to supply labor to install the replacement, and refused to supply a rental car while this took place. They had the nerve to tell us they wasted three hours dealing with warrantee process, while we had months of headaches, hundreds in rental car fees and seemingly never ending frustrations in dealing with this dealership.</text>
